**Consumer Complaint Classification \- Niranjan Galla**

**📋 Project Overview**

This project performs multi-class text classification on consumer complaint data to automatically categorize complaints into predefined product categories using machine learning.

**🎯 Objective**

Classify consumer complaints into one of four categories:

* Credit reporting, repair, or other  
    
* Debt collection  
    
* Consumer Loan  
    
* Mortgage

📊 **Dataset Analysis**

**Dataset Statistics**

Total Complaints: 515,519

Categories: 3 product types

Data Source: Consumer Complaint Database

**🔧 Data Preprocessing**

**Text Cleaning Steps**

* Lowercasing \- Convert all text to lowercase  
    
* Punctuation Removal \- Remove special characters and punctuation  
    
* Number Removal \- Eliminate numerical values  
    
* Stopword Removal \- Filter out common English stopwords  
    
* Tokenization \- Split text into individual words  
    
* Text Normalization \- Clean and standardize text format

**Word Cloud Visualization**

![][image3]![][image4]

Word clouds showing most frequent terms in each complaint category

**🔡 Feature Engineering**

**TF-IDF Vectorization**

* Features: 2,000 most important terms  
    
* N-grams: Unigrams and bigrams (1,2)  
    
* Vocabulary Size: 2,000 features  
    
* Sparsity: Optimized for efficient processing

**Train-Test Split**

* Training Set: 412,415 samples (80%)  
    
* Testing Set: 103,104 samples (20%)  
    
* Stratified Sampling: Maintains class distribution

**🤖 Model Training & Comparison**

**Models Evaluated**

* Logistic Regression \- Fast and interpretable  
    
* Naive Bayes \- Probabilistic classifier  
    
* Random Forest \- Ensemble method  
    
* Support Vector Machine (SVM) \- Maximum margin classifier

**🎯 Key Findings**

**Performance Insights**

**High Accuracy:** Models achieved \~97% accuracy on test data

**Class Imbalance:** Debt collection complaints dominate the dataset

**Feature Importance:** TF-IDF with bigrams captures important context

**Model Selection:** Logistic Regression performed best with optimal speed-accuracy balance

**🚀 Quick Start**

**Prerequisites**

Python 3.8+

**Git**

**1\. Clone the Repository**

bash  
git clone https://github.com/your-username/consumer-complaint-classification.git  
cd consumer-complaint-classification

**2\. Install Dependencies**

bash  
pip install \-r requirements.txt

**3\. Download the Dataset**

Download the Consumer Complaint Database from data.gov and place it in the project root as complaints.csv

**4\. Run the Project**

bash

\# Open the notebook  
jupyter notebook notebooks/consumer\_complaint\_classification.ipynb

\# Or run as script  
python run\_pipeline.py
